<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="440" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="45.[1433,2641,1400,2375]" pageId="45" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1435,1781,2106,2139]" pageId="45" pageNumber="440">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Virtually nothing is known of the ecology and threats of Osgood’s Small-eared Shrew, but it is known from a relatively wide distribution compared with other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[2210,2321,2184,2217]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="45" pageNumber="440" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cryptotis</taxonomicName>
. Osgood’s Small-eared Shrew might be threatened by habitat destruction from deforestation for agricultural expansion, but if it is similar to the Ecuadorean Small-eared Shrew, it might be resillent in degraded regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
